22:19.170 --> 22:20.159
Really?

22:20.960 --> 22:23.121
You make people feel
the things you're feeling.

22:23.500 --> 22:24.910
I want to be able to do that.

22:25.840 --> 22:28.297
A couple of hours
a couple of nights a week.

22:28.380 --> 22:29.927
Chips and salsa on me.

22:31.970 --> 22:33.961
"Stephie Moore is mean.

22:34.060 --> 22:35.300
She..."

22:35.390 --> 22:36.379
Sic.

22:36.770 --> 22:38.681
"She so stupid."

22:38.770 --> 22:40.146
Third grade!

22:40.650 --> 22:42.106
I was in third grade!

22:43.320 --> 22:45.891
Don't get what my grade school diaries
have to do with anything.

22:45.990 --> 22:47.059
Well...

22:47.190 --> 22:50.774
First, there's a bunch of
gifted child drama I won't get into.

22:51.200 --> 22:54.283
The main thing is,
you have to tell the truth in poetry.

22:54.580 --> 22:55.569
Your truth.

22:56.000 --> 22:57.444
-But--
-No buts.

22:57.540 --> 22:59.747
EX n/h/lo n/h/l ﬁt.

23:00.330 --> 23:02.412
"Out of nothing comes nothing."

23:04.420 --> 23:08.083
I just don't like it when people
read my... things.

