32:29.230 --> 32:31.812
You knew the shit
I shared was personal.

32:31.900 --> 32:35.233
You knew where it came from,
and that it would get people talking.

32:36.660 --> 32:39.481
I realize now I was desperate
for someone to listen...

32:40.910 --> 32:42.116
and you listened.

32:43.540 --> 32:47.203
And then you made my most
private thoughts a public spectacle.

32:50.960 --> 32:52.587
[bell rings]

32:54.130 --> 32:55.506
[Jessica] It's her writing.

32:55.760 --> 32:57.216
I can totally recognize it.

32:57.970 --> 33:00.177
[Courtney] Why would she write
something like this?

33:00.270 --> 33:01.510
So humiliating.

33:02.600 --> 33:04.591
[teacher] It has been
brought to my attention

33:04.690 --> 33:07.727
that Ryan's publication
now includes poetry.

33:07.900 --> 33:10.027
And since we're doing sonnets
this semester,

33:10.110 --> 33:13.523
and since you're all going to be
distracted by it anyway,

33:13.610 --> 33:17.569
I thought we would take a minute
to parse the work of this poet.

33:17.950 --> 33:19.690
-[coughs] Hannah.
-[class chuckling]

33:19.780 --> 33:22.783
[teacher] There's a sort of naked
vulnerability to it that I like.

33:22.870 --> 33:23.996
It's quite intimate.

33:24.410 --> 33:25.320
[all laugh]

33:25.870 --> 33:27.622
"Intimate" is not a dirty word.

33:30.250 --> 33:33.003
"Today I am wearing lacy black underwear

33:33.090 --> 33:34.967
for the sole purpose of knowing..."

