35:20.990 --> 35:22.560
The ambulance is already there.

35:24.030 --> 35:25.156
And the cops.

35:26.080 --> 35:28.457
And the front door's open.
I run inside.

35:30.290 --> 35:31.951
Her parents are there.

35:32.960 --> 35:33.995
And she's...

35:36.710 --> 35:38.200
They've got her in a body bag.

35:40.510 --> 35:43.343
I remember thinking,
"There's no handles on that bag-

35:43.430 --> 35:46.638
How are they gonna pick her up?
How are they gonna carry her?"

35:48.520 --> 35:50.385
And they just grabbed the bag...

35:51.190 --> 35:53.306
and threw her in the ambulance.

35:55.730 --> 35:56.719
Just like that.

36:07.910 --> 36:09.150
[Clay sniffling]

36:21.170 --> 36:22.376
Do the other kids know?

36:26.430 --> 36:29.137
Why you're taking care of Hannah
like you are?

36:31.180 --> 36:32.260
Of course not.

36:34.020 --> 36:35.180
You needed to know.

36:38.780 --> 36:39.974
You're my friend.

36:47.490 --> 36:48.570
What the hell, Ryan?

36:48.660 --> 36:52.118
Hannah. What's so secret
you couldn't speak to me at school?

36:52.250 --> 36:54.457
